ndicates failure.\nThe subtask is successful if:\n1.  The **number of bubbles eliminated** has increased significantly.\n2.  The cluster of bubbles **closest to the cannon** has been reduced in size.\n3.  The action was executed with the correct mouse click coordinates (A, B).\n4.  The shot was fired at the target cluster, causing a chain reaction.\n4. If the last action is not executed successfully, what is the most probable cause? How to improve this action?\nYou should give only one cause and refer to the following rules:\nThe subtask failed if:\n1.  The shot did not connect to a cluster (no elimination).\n2.  The shot cleared a cluster but **failed to clear the sector closest to the cannon**.\n3.  The shot caused a **chain reaction** that cleared a large area, but the central zone was still under threat.\n4.  The shot was **misdirected**, clearing a sector that was not the most urgent threat.\n- If there is an error message for the last executed action provided in the above information, analyze the cause based on the report, otherwise, you should regard that there are no error messages.\n- You are not allowed to guess the error message by yourself.\n5. Is the subtask completed? Give your reasons.\nYou MUST remember that the subtask is completed ONLY if The subtask is completed if the action successfully eliminated bubbles and/or cleared the most urgent threat sector, and the new state is stable for the next subtask..\n6. Do you think the subtask is reasonable? Give your reasons.\nSuccess: You need to output whether the last action was executed successfully or not.\n- If the last action is successful, you should only output 'True'. Otherwise, you should only output 'False'.\n\n\n\nYou should only respond in the format described below.\nReasoning:\n1. ...\n2. ...\n3. ...\n4. ...\n5. ...\n6. ...\nSuccess:\nTrue"}]}], 'model': 'qwen3-vl-plus', 'max_tokens': 1024, 'temperature': 0.0}}
